title: How to Make Peach Slice

steps.headline: Grease and line two bar tins or one lamington tin.
Place cake mixture in a large bowl.
Rub butter into cake mix with finger tips, stir through coconut.
Press into tins, bake for 15 minutes.
steps.description: Remove from heat allow to cool.

steps.headline: Drain peaches and place neatly over top.
Sprinkle cinnamon and brown sugar over the top.
Lightly beat eggs and sour cream together, pour over top of slice.

text: Preheat oven to 200°C.  Grease and line two bar tins or one lamington tin.  Place cake mixture in a large bowl.  Chop butter into cubes.  Rub butter into cake mix with finger tips, stir through coconut.  Press into tins, bake for 15 minutes. Remove from heat allow to cool. Drain peaches and place neatly over top.  Sprinkle cinnamon and brown sugar over the top.  Lightly beat eggs and sour cream together, pour over top of slice.  Bake for a further 15 minutes.  Cut into serving size slices.  Finished.
